}}As of the 2020 census there were 1,055 people, 526 housing units, and 535 families. There were 944 [[White Americans|White]] people, 0 [[African Americans]], 30 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 12 [[Asian Americans|Asians]], 1 [[Pacific Islander]], 10 people from some other race, and 58 people from two or more races. 29 people were of [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile?g=160XX00US4165450 |access-date=2023-05-24 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The ancestry in Saunders Lake was 20.2% [[English Americans|English]], 18.1% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 17.1% [[German Americans|German]], 7.6% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 5.0% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], and 1.5% [[French Americans|French]].<ref name=":0" />

The median age was 42.6 years old. 16.6% of the population were older than 65, with 11.5% from 65 to 74, 3.9% from 75 to 84, and 1.2% from ages older than 85.<ref name=":0" />

Even though the median income was recorded, families had $185,022, and non-families had $16,544. 6.4% of the population were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />{{clear left}}

